1
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:23,390
I should've known that you would
be here. Professor McGonagall.

2
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:37,197
Good evening. Professor Dumbledore.

3
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,478
Are the rumors true. Albus?

4
00:01:42,719 --> 00:01:47,713
I'm afraid so. professor.
The good and the bad.

5
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:51,037
-And the boy?
-Hagrid is bringing him.

6
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:55,034
Is it wise to trust Hagrid
with something so important?

7
00:01:55,519 --> 00:02:00,229
Professor. I would trust Hagrid
with my life.

8
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:22,279
Professor Dumbledore. sir.
Professor McGonagall.

9
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:26,189
-No problems. I trust. Hagrid?
-No. sir.

10
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:30,678
Little tyke fell asleep
as we were flying over Bristol.

11
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,829
Try not to wake him.

12
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,591
There you go.

13
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:46,157
Do you really think it's safe.
leaving him with these people?

14
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:51,388
I've watched them all day.
They're the worst sort of Muggles.

15
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:55,427
-They really are--
-The only family he has.

16
00:02:55,680 --> 00:03:00,390
He'll be famous. Every child
in our world will know his name.

17
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:02,277
Exactly.

18
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:06,598
He's far better off growing up
away from all of that.

19
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:11,599
Until he's ready.

20
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:28,399
There. there. Hagrid.
It's not really goodbye. after all.

21
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,193
Good luck...

22
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,229
...Harry Potter.

23
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:03,958
Up. Get up!

24
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,913
Now!

25
00:04:21,039 --> 00:04:24,270
Wake up. cousin!
We're going to the zoo!

26
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:40,074
-Here he comes. the birthday boy.
-Happy birthday. son.

27
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:44,877
Cook breakfast.
And try not to burn anything.

28
00:04:45,079 --> 00:04:49,834
-Yes. Aunt Petunia.
-I want everything to be perfect...

29
00:04:50,039 --> 00:04:52,837
...for my Dudley's special day!

30
00:04:53,039 --> 00:04:57,829
-Hurry up! Bring my coffee. boy.
-Yes. Uncle Vernon.

31
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,992
Aren't they wonderful. darling?

32
00:05:04,079 --> 00:05:07,435
-How many are there?
-36. Counted them myself.

33
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:10,712
36?! But last year I had 37!

34
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:14,629
-But some are bigger than last year's.
-I don't care!

35
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:17,229
This is what we're going to do.

36
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:21,638
We're going to buy you two
new presents. How's that. pumpkin?

37
00:05:23,519 --> 00:05:28,912
It should be a lovely day at the zoo.
I'm really looking forward to it.

38
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,832
l'm warning you now. boy.

39
00:05:34,039 --> 00:05:37,395
Any funny business. any at all...

40
00:05:37,599 --> 00:05:40,511
...and you won't have
any meals for a week.

41
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,912
Get in.

42
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:52,109
Make it move.

43
00:05:54,679 --> 00:05:56,317
Move!

44
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,915
-Move!
-He's asleep!

45
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,554
He's boring.

46
00:06:03,879 --> 00:06:05,278
Sorry about him.

47
00:06:05,479 --> 00:06:09,028
He doesn't understand
what it's like. lying there...

48
00:06:09,599 --> 00:06:13,228
...watching people press
their ugly faces in on you.

49
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:18,440
Can you hear me?

50
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:24,719
It's just. I've never talked
to a snake before.

51
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,513
Do you...?

52
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:30,679
Do you talk to people often?

53
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,911
You're from Burma. aren't you?
Was it nice there?

54
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:37,315
Do you miss your family?

55
00:06:40,079 --> 00:06:44,595
| see. That's me as well.
I never knew my parents either.

56
00:06:44,799 --> 00:06:49,589
Mummy. Dad. you won't believe
what this snake is doing!

57
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,671
Thanks.

58
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:15,233
Anytime.

59
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,271
Snake!

60
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:38,317
Mum! Mummy! Help me!

61
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:41,552
My darling boy!
How did you get in there?

62
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:46,909
Who did this? How did you get
in there? Is there a snake?

63
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:56,674
It's all right. sweetheart.
We'll get you out of these cold clothes.

64
00:07:58,359 --> 00:08:01,157
-What happened?
-I swear. I don't know!

65
00:08:01,359 --> 00:08:05,068
The glass was there
and then it was gone. like magic.

66
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:11,993
There's no such thing as magic.

67
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:49,840
Marge is ill. Ate a funny whelk.

68
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:53,112
-Dad. look! Harry's got a letter!
-|t's mine!

69
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:55,959
Yours? Who'd be writing to you?

70
00:09:25,959 --> 00:09:30,316
No more mail through this letterbox.

71
00:09:41,999 --> 00:09:44,718
Have a lovely day at the office. dear.

72
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:50,040
Shoo! Go on.

73
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:16,632
Fine day. Sunday.

74
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:21,711
In my opinion. best day of the week.
Why is that. Dudley?

75
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:26,152
-Because there's no post on Sundays?
-Right you are. Harry!

76
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,999
No post on Sunday.

77
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:34,114
No blasted letters today! No. sir.

78
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:39,435
Not one single bloody letter. Not one!

79
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:51,229
No. sir. not one blasted. miserable--

80
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:04,396
Make it stop. please!

81
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,951
Stop it!

82
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:14,753
Mummy. what's happening?

83
00:11:18,039 --> 00:11:22,191
Give me that! Give me that letter!

84
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:26,392
Get off!

85
00:11:29,999 --> 00:11:33,992
They're my letters! Let go of me!

86
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,678
That's it! We're going away!

87
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:41,835
Far away. where they can't find us!

88
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:45,156
Daddy's gone mad. hasn't he?

89
00:12:18,639 --> 00:12:20,834
Make a wish. Harry.

90
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:38,236
Who's there?

91
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:52,229
Sorry about that.

92
00:12:58,839 --> 00:13:03,230
I demand that you leave at once.
You are breaking and entering.

93
00:13:05,999 --> 00:13:08,718
Dry up. Dursley. you great prune.

94
00:13:13,719 --> 00:13:17,075
I haven't seen you
since you was a baby. Harry.

95
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:21,637
You're a bit more along than I expected.
Particularly in the middle.

96
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:24,559
I'm not Harry.

97
00:13:26,319 --> 00:13:29,868
-I am.
-Well. of course you are.

98
00:13:30,639 --> 00:13:32,152
Got something for you.

99
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:37,718
Afraid | sat on it. but I imagine
it'll taste fine just the same.

100
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:43,396
Baked it myself. words and all.

101
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:49,709
Thank you.

102
00:13:49,959 --> 00:13:53,918
It's not every day your young man
turns 11. is it?

103
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:12,439
Excuse me. but who are you?

104
00:14:12,639 --> 00:14:17,349
Rubeus Hagrid. Keeper of Keys
and Grounds at Hogwarts.

105
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:21,149
-Of course. you know about Hogwarts.
-Sorry. no.

106
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:26,430
Didn't you ever wonder where
your mum and dad learned it all?

107
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:27,999
Learned what?

108
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,634
You're a wizard. Harry.

109
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:33,756
-|'m a what?
-A wizard.

110
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:36,872
A good one. I'd wager.
once you're trained up.

111
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:39,873
No. you've made a mistake.
I mean...

112
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:42,958
...I can't be a wizard.

113
00:14:43,599 --> 00:14:48,150
I mean. I'm just Harry. Just Harry.

114
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:53,034
Well. Just Harry. did you ever
make anything happen?

115
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:57,711
Anything you couldn't explain.
when you were angry or scared?

116
00:15:13,439 --> 00:15:16,431
IIDear Mr. Potter.
We are pleased to accept you...

117
00:15:16,639 --> 00:15:19,756
...at Hogwarts School
of Witchcraft and Wizardry.II

118
00:15:19,959 --> 00:15:24,714
He will not be going! We swore
we'd put a stop to all this rubbish.

119
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:28,959
You knew? You knew all along
and you never told me?

120
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:32,118
Of course we knew.
How could you not be?

121
00:15:32,319 --> 00:15:35,868
My perfect sister being who she was.

122
00:15:36,079 --> 00:15:41,790
My mother and father were so proud
the day she got her letter.

123
00:15:41,999 --> 00:15:45,992
IIWe have a witch in the family.
Isn't it wonderful?II

124
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:49,715
l was the only one to see her
for what she was.

125
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:51,592
A freak!

126
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:54,633
Then she met that Potter.
and then she had you...

127
00:15:54,839 --> 00:16:00,311
...and I knew you would be the same.
Just as strange. just as abnormal.

128
00:16:00,519 --> 00:16:05,309
And then she got herself blown up.
and we got landed with you.

129
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:09,354
Blown up? You told me
my parents died in a car crash.

130
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:13,718
A car crash? A car crash killed
Lily and James Potter?

131
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:17,674
-We had to say something.
-|t's an outrage! A scandal!

132
00:16:17,879 --> 00:16:20,234
He'll not be going.

133
00:16:20,439 --> 00:16:23,636
A great Muggle like you
is going to stop him?

134
00:16:23,799 --> 00:16:24,788
Muggle?

135
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:28,954
Non-magic folk. This boy's had
his name down since he were born.

136
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:32,869
He's going to the finest school
of witchcraft and wizardry.

137
00:16:33,079 --> 00:16:38,756
He'll be under the finest headmaster
Hogwarts has seen. Albus Dumbledore.

138
00:16:38,959 --> 00:16:43,555
I will not pay to have a crackpot
old fool teach him magic tricks.

139
00:16:43,759 --> 00:16:48,116
Never insult Albus Dumbledore...

140
00:16:48,319 --> 00:16:50,275
...in front of me.

141
00:17:07,439 --> 00:17:12,467
I'd appreciate it if you didn't tell
anyone at Hogwarts about that.

142
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:16,633
-|'m not allowed to do magic.
-Okay.

143
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:20,758
We're a bit behind schedule.
Best be off.

144
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:29,752
Unless you'd rather stay. of course.

145
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:46,630
IIAll students must be equipped with...

146
00:17:46,839 --> 00:17:49,637
...one standard size 2
pewter cauldron...

147
00:17:49,839 --> 00:17:55,391
...and may bring. if they desire.
either an owl. a cat or a toad.II

148
00:17:55,639 --> 00:17:58,107
Can we find all this in London?

149
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,595
If you know where to go.

150
00:18:22,439 --> 00:18:25,272
Ah. Hagrid! The usual. I presume?

151
00:18:25,479 --> 00:18:29,188
No. thanks. Tom.
I'm on official Hogwarts business.

152
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:32,358
Just helping Harry buy
his school supplies.

153
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:35,990
Bless my soul.
lt's Harry Potter!

154
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:43,430
Welcome back. Mr. Potter.
Welcome back.

155
00:18:43,639 --> 00:18:47,791
Doris Crockford. I can't believe
I'm meeting you at last.

156
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:53,268
Harry Potter. Can't tell you
how pleased I am to meet you.

157
00:18:53,479 --> 00:18:55,913
Hello. professor. I didn't see you.

158
00:18:56,119 --> 00:19:00,909
Professor Quirrell will be your
Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher.

159
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,429
Oh. nice to meet you.

160
00:19:03,679 --> 00:19:06,637
Fearfully fascinating subject.

161
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:11,277
Not that you need it. eh. Potter?

162
00:19:12,159 --> 00:19:16,152
Yes. well. must be going now.
Lots to buy.

163
00:19:16,359 --> 00:19:18,031
Goodbye.

164
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:24,076
-See. Harry? You're famous.
-But why am | famous?

165
00:19:24,279 --> 00:19:27,589
All those people.
how is it they know who I am?

166
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:31,429
I'm not sure I'm the right person
to tell you that.

167
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:51,355
Welcome. Harry. to Diagon Alley.

168
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:09,428
Here. you get your quills and ink.

169
00:20:09,679 --> 00:20:13,433
Over there. all your bits and bobs
for doing wizardry.

170
00:20:37,279 --> 00:20:39,429
It's a world-class racing broom.

171
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:43,349
Look at it! The new Nimbus 2000!

172
00:20:43,599 --> 00:20:46,750
It's the fastest model yet.

173
00:20:50,319 --> 00:20:54,710
But how am | to pay for all this?
I haven't any money.

174
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:58,151
There's your money.
Gringotts. the wizard bank.

175
00:20:58,360 --> 00:21:03,639
Ain't no safer place. not one.
Except perhaps Hogwarts.

176
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:19,594
Hagrid. what exactly
are these things?

177
00:21:19,799 --> 00:21:24,827
They're goblins. Clever as they come.
but not the most friendly of beasts.

178
00:21:25,039 --> 00:21:26,916
Best stay close.

179
00:21:30,799 --> 00:21:34,314
Mr. Harry Potter wishes
to make a withdrawal.

180
00:21:38,359 --> 00:21:41,396
And does Mr. Harry Potter
have his key?

181
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:45,392
Wait a minute.
Got it here somewhere.

182
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:50,839
Ha! There's the little devil.

183
00:21:51,039 --> 00:21:53,792
And there's something else as well.

184
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:58,197
Professor Dumbledore gave me this.

185
00:22:02,079 --> 00:22:06,948
It's about You-Know-What
in vault you-know-which.

186
00:22:08,199 --> 00:22:10,076
Very well.

187
00:22:15,079 --> 00:22:17,798
Vault 687.

188
00:22:19,639 --> 00:22:21,834
Lamp. please.

189
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,274
Key. please.

190
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:57,355
Did you think your parents
would leave you with nothing?

191
00:22:58,599 --> 00:23:02,148
-Vault 713.
-What's in there. Hagrid?

192
00:23:02,359 --> 00:23:06,352
Can't tell you.
Hogwarts business. Very secret.

193
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,079
Stand back.

194
00:23:35,199 --> 00:23:37,872
Best not to mention this to anyone.

195
00:23:45,959 --> 00:23:49,713
I still need a wand.

196
00:23:49,919 --> 00:23:53,195
You want Ollivanders.
There ain't no place better.

197
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:58,795
Run along there and wait.
I got one more thing to do.

198
00:24:16,039 --> 00:24:17,791
Hello?

199
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:22,392
Hello?

200
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:29,878
I wondered when
I'd be seeing you. Mr. Potter.

201
00:24:37,359 --> 00:24:39,475
It seems only yesterday...

202
00:24:39,719 --> 00:24:45,316
...that your mother and father were
in here buying their first wands.

203
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:53,915
Here we are.

204
00:25:02,159 --> 00:25:04,593
Give it a wave.

205
00:25:10,799 --> 00:25:13,233
Apparently not.

206
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:22,476
Perhaps...

207
00:25:24,080 --> 00:25:26,150
...this.

208
00:25:32,919 --> 00:25:37,356
No. no. definitely not.
No matter.

209
00:25:44,279 --> 00:25:45,837
I wonder....

210
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:16,035
Curious.

211
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:19,038
Very curious.

212
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:22,232
Sorry. but what's curious?

213
00:26:23,879 --> 00:26:27,030
I remember every wand
I've ever sold. Mr. Potter.

214
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:29,879
It so happens that the phoenix...

215
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:34,596
...whose tail feather resides
in your wand. gave another feather.

216
00:26:34,999 --> 00:26:37,957
Just one other.

217
00:26:38,159 --> 00:26:42,311
It is curious that you should
be destined for this wand...

218
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:47,998
...when its brother
gave you that scar.

219
00:26:49,759 --> 00:26:52,831
And who owned that wand?

220
00:26:53,639 --> 00:26:55,948
We do not speak his name.

221
00:26:56,399 --> 00:26:59,755
The wand chooses
the wizard. Mr. Potter.

222
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:02,838
It's not always clear why.

223
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:06,556
But I think it is clear...

224
00:27:06,759 --> 00:27:10,513
...that we can expect
great things from you.

225
00:27:10,719 --> 00:27:14,792
After all. He-Who-Must-Not-Be-Named . ..

226
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:17,600
...did great things.

227
00:27:17,799 --> 00:27:19,710
Terrible...

228
00:27:20,159 --> 00:27:23,276
...yes. but great.

229
00:27:28,679 --> 00:27:30,635
Harry! Harry!

230
00:27:30,999 --> 00:27:33,274
Happy birthday.

231
00:27:40,119 --> 00:27:43,475
You all right. Harry?
You seem very quiet.

232
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:49,198
He killed my parents. didn't he?
The one who gave me this.

233
00:27:49,399 --> 00:27:52,869
You know. Hagrid. I know you do.

234
00:27:56,600 --> 00:28:00,957
First. and understand this
because it's very important:

235
00:28:01,159 --> 00:28:03,593
Not all wizards are good.

236
00:28:03,799 --> 00:28:06,188
Some of them go bad.
A few years ago...

237
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:11,190
...there was a wizard who went as bad
as you can go. His name was V--

238
00:28:11,399 --> 00:28:14,869
-His name was V--
-Maybe if you wrote it down?

239
00:28:15,080 --> 00:28:16,877
No. I can't spell it.

240
00:28:17,080 --> 00:28:21,153
-All right. Voldemort.
-Vo|demort?

241
00:28:24,959 --> 00:28:27,109
It was dark times. Harry.

242
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:32,312
Voldemort started
to gather some followers.

243
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:35,757
Brought them over to the Dark Side.

244
00:28:37,079 --> 00:28:40,071
Anyone that stood up to him
ended up dead.

245
00:28:41,159 --> 00:28:44,071
Your parents fought against him.

246
00:28:44,279 --> 00:28:47,908
But nobody lived once
