your broom. I want you to mount it.

491
00:53:41,199 --> 00:53:45,033
Grip it tight. You don't wanna be
sliding off the end.

492
00:53:45,399 --> 00:53:50,154
When I blow my whistle. I want you
to kick off from the ground. hard.

493
00:53:50,360 --> 00:53:54,035
Keep your broom steady.
hover for a moment...

494
00:53:54,239 --> 00:53:58,357
...then lean forward slightly
and touch back down.

495
00:53:58,599 --> 00:54:01,591
On my whistle. Three. two....

496
00:54:03,920 --> 00:54:05,239
Mr. Longbottom.

497
00:54:09,680 --> 00:54:12,433
-Mr. Longbottom!
-Down. down!

498
00:54:12,640 --> 00:54:13,834
Neville!

499
00:54:17,399 --> 00:54:19,959
Come back down this instant!

500
00:54:47,760 --> 00:54:50,035
Everyone out of the way!

501
00:54:55,360 --> 00:54:57,430
Is he all right?

502
00:54:57,799 --> 00:55:03,237
Oh. dear. it's a broken wrist.
Poor boy. Come on now. up you get.

503
00:55:04,480 --> 00:55:08,951
Keep your feet on the ground
while I take him to the hospital wing.

504
00:55:09,159 --> 00:55:12,674
Understand? If I see
a single broom in the air...

505
00:55:12,880 --> 00:55:17,908
...the one riding it will be expelled
before they can say Ouidditch.

506
00:55:18,119 --> 00:55:19,950
Did you see his face?

507
00:55:20,160 --> 00:55:23,835
If he had squeezed this. he'd have
remembered to fall on his arse.

508
00:55:24,039 --> 00:55:26,428
Give it here. Malfoy.

509
00:55:27,239 --> 00:55:30,788
No. I'll leave it somewhere
for Longbottom to find.

510
00:55:34,800 --> 00:55:37,155
How about on the roof?

511
00:55:38,279 --> 00:55:41,954
What's the matter. Potter?
Bit beyond your reach?

512
00:55:44,360 --> 00:55:48,035
Harry. no way!
You heard what Madam Hooch said.

513
00:55:48,240 --> 00:55:51,038
Besides. you don't know how to fly.

514
00:55:51,319 --> 00:55:53,150
What an idiot.

515
00:55:56,360 --> 00:55:59,750
Give it here or I'll
knock you off your broom!

516
00:55:59,960 --> 00:56:01,996
Is that so?

517
00:56:04,999 --> 00:56:07,194
Have it your way. then.

518
00:56:38,599 --> 00:56:42,069
-Nice going. Harry.
-That was wicked. Harry!

519
00:56:42,279 --> 00:56:44,235
Harry Potter!

520
00:56:45,159 --> 00:56:47,070
Follow me.

521
00:56:58,279 --> 00:57:00,429
You wait here.

522
00:57:02,120 --> 00:57:07,194
Professor Ouirrell. excuse me.
Could I borrow Wood for a moment?

523
00:57:07,399 --> 00:57:09,151
Yes. of course.

524
00:57:14,600 --> 00:57:20,118
Potter. this is Oliver Wood.
Wood. l have found you a Seeker.

525
00:57:22,119 --> 00:57:25,475
Have you heard? Harry Potter's
the new Gryffindor Seeker.

526
00:57:25,720 --> 00:57:27,836
| always knew he'd do well.

527
00:57:28,279 --> 00:57:32,158
Seeker? But first years
never make the house teams.

528
00:57:32,360 --> 00:57:36,672
-You must be the youngest player in--
-A century. McGonagall says.

529
00:57:36,880 --> 00:57:39,394
Well done. Harry.
Wood's just told us.

530
00:57:39,600 --> 00:57:41,989
Fred and George are on the team.
Beaters.

531
00:57:42,199 --> 00:57:45,748
Our job is to make sure you
don't get bloodied up too bad.

532
00:57:45,959 --> 00:57:48,519
Can't make any promises.
Rough game. Ouidditch.

533
00:57:48,719 --> 00:57:52,507
But no one's died in years.
Someone vanishes occasionally.

534
00:57:52,720 --> 00:57:55,359
But they'll turn up in a month or two.

535
00:57:55,600 --> 00:58:00,993
Go on. Ouidditch is great. Best game
there is. and you'll be great too.

536
00:58:01,200 --> 00:58:04,272
I've never played.
What if I make a fool of myself?

537
00:58:04,679 --> 00:58:09,275
You won't make a fool of yourself.
It's in your blood.

538
00:58:17,479 --> 00:58:21,154
You never told me your father
was a Seeker too.

539
00:58:21,959 --> 00:58:24,075
I didn't know.

540
00:58:28,400 --> 00:58:32,791
I'm telling you. it's spooky.
She knows more about you than you do.

541
00:58:32,999 --> 00:58:35,194
Who doesn't?

542
00:58:36,080 --> 00:58:38,116
What's happening?

543
00:58:38,320 --> 00:58:42,359
The staircases change. remember?

544
00:58:47,600 --> 00:58:51,878
-Let's go this way.
-Before the staircase moves again.

545
00:58:59,200 --> 00:59:02,476
Does anybody feel like
we shouldn't be here?

546
00:59:02,720 --> 00:59:04,756
We're not supposed to be here.

547
00:59:04,960 --> 00:59:08,714
This is the third floor.
lt's forbidden.

548
00:59:09,840 --> 00:59:11,353
Let's go.

549
00:59:13,480 --> 00:59:16,233
-|t's Filch's cat!
-Run!

550
00:59:19,879 --> 00:59:23,076
Ouick. let's hide through that door!

551
00:59:28,000 --> 00:59:29,956
-|t's locked!
-We're done for!

552
00:59:30,160 --> 00:59:32,230
Move over!

553
00:59:33,159 --> 00:59:35,195
Alohomora.

554
00:59:36,039 --> 00:59:37,870
Get in.

555
00:59:39,079 --> 00:59:40,114
Alohomora?

556
00:59:40,319 --> 00:59:42,753
Standard Book of Spells,
chapter seven.

557
00:59:42,959 --> 00:59:46,190
Anyone here. my sweet?

558
00:59:52,199 --> 00:59:53,154
Come on.

559
00:59:54,000 --> 00:59:56,355
-Fi|ch is gone.
-He thinks this door's locked.

560
00:59:56,600 --> 01:00:00,070
-It was locked.
-And for good reason.

561
01:00:24,719 --> 01:00:29,952
What are they doing. keeping a thing
like that locked up in a school?

562
01:00:30,160 --> 01:00:33,675
Didn't you see what
it was standing on?

563
01:00:33,879 --> 01:00:37,872
I wasn't looking at its feet!
I was preoccupied with its heads.

564
01:00:38,079 --> 01:00:40,832
Or maybe you didn't notice.
There were three!

565
01:00:41,040 --> 01:00:44,555
It was standing on a trap door.
It wasn't there by accident.

566
01:00:44,759 --> 01:00:48,149
-|t's guarding something.
-Guarding something?

567
01:00:48,560 --> 01:00:52,155
That's right. Now. if you two don't mind.
I'm going to bed...

568
01:00:52,359 --> 01:00:55,829
...before you come up with another idea
to get us killed.

569
01:00:56,039 --> 01:00:59,031
Or worse. expelled.

570
01:01:02,159 --> 01:01:06,232
She needs to sort out her priorities.

571
01:01:10,680 --> 01:01:14,719
Ouidditch is easy to understand.
Each team has seven players.

572
01:01:14,920 --> 01:01:20,392
Three Chasers. two Beaters.
one Keeper and a Seeker. That's you.

573
01:01:25,279 --> 01:01:29,238
There are three kinds of balls.
This one's called the Ouaffle.

574
01:01:29,440 --> 01:01:35,151
The Chasers handle the Ouaffle and try
to put it through one of those hoops.

575
01:01:35,360 --> 01:01:39,558
The Keeper. that's me.
defends the hoops. With me so far?

576
01:01:39,759 --> 01:01:44,037
I think so. What are those?

577
01:01:46,240 --> 01:01:48,310
You better take this.

578
01:01:57,959 --> 01:02:00,632
Careful now. it's coming back.

579
01:02:06,960 --> 01:02:10,430
Not bad. Potter.
You'd make a fair Beater.

580
01:02:26,400 --> 01:02:28,595
What was that?

581
01:02:29,320 --> 01:02:32,915
Bludger. Nasty little buggers.

582
01:02:33,120 --> 01:02:36,476
But you are a Seeker.

583
01:02:39,920 --> 01:02:44,311
The only thing I want you
to worry about is this.

584
01:02:44,559 --> 01:02:46,948
The Golden Snitch.

585
01:02:47,159 --> 01:02:50,037
-I like this ball.
-You like it now.

586
01:02:50,240 --> 01:02:54,074
Just wait. lt's wicked fast
and damn near impossible to see.

587
01:02:54,279 --> 01:02:56,156
What do I do with it?

588
01:02:56,359 --> 01:02:59,476
You catch it.
Before the other team's Seeker.

589
01:02:59,720 --> 01:03:02,075
You catch this. the game's over.

590
01:03:02,279 --> 01:03:06,067
You catch this. Potter.
and we win.

591
01:03:14,759 --> 01:03:19,879
One of a wizard's most rudimentary
skills is levitation...

592
01:03:20,080 --> 01:03:23,868
...or the ability to make objects fly.

593
01:03:24,079 --> 01:03:26,388
Do you have your feathers? Good.

594
01:03:26,640 --> 01:03:31,555
Now. don't forget the nice wrist
movement we've been practicing.

595
01:03:31,760 --> 01:03:34,957
The swish and flick. Everyone.

596
01:03:35,480 --> 01:03:40,873
The swish and flick. Good.
Oh. and enunciate.

597
01:03:41,559 --> 01:03:45,677
Wingardium l.eviosa.
Off you go. then.

598
01:03:46,679 --> 01:03:49,068
Wingardium l. e viosa .

599
01:03:49,319 --> 01:03:51,549
Wingardium l. e viosa .

600
01:03:55,239 --> 01:03:59,312
No. stop. stop. stop! You're going
to take someone's eye out.

601
01:03:59,559 --> 01:04:05,270
Besides. you're saying it wrong.
It's l.eviosa, not l.eviosar.

602
01:04:05,840 --> 01:04:09,879
You do it then. if you're so clever.
Go on. go on.

603
01:04:11,079 --> 01:04:14,037
Wingardium L e viosa .

604
01:04:21,240 --> 01:04:26,633
Well done! See here. everyone.
Miss Granger's done it!

605
01:04:26,839 --> 01:04:28,431
Splendid!

606
01:04:29,959 --> 01:04:32,075
Well done. dear.

607
01:04:36,119 --> 01:04:40,032
I think we're going to need
another feather over here.

608
01:04:46,279 --> 01:04:50,352
IIlt's Leviosa, not Leviosar. "

609
01:04:50,599 --> 01:04:55,719
She's a nightmare. honestly!
No wonder she hasn't got any friends.

610
01:04:56,359 --> 01:04:58,793
I think she heard you.

611
01:05:26,279 --> 01:05:28,270
Where's Hermione?

612
01:05:28,480 --> 01:05:31,472
Parvati said she wouldn't
come out of the bathroom.

613
01:05:31,680 --> 01:05:35,593
She said that she'd been in there
all afternoon. crying.

614
01:05:39,840 --> 01:05:43,355
Troll in the dungeon!

615
01:05:43,599 --> 01:05:46,796
Troll in the dungeon!

616
01:05:49,479 --> 01:05:51,709
Thought you ought to know.

617
01:05:58,320 --> 01:06:01,039
Silence!

618
01:06:02,560 --> 01:06:06,439
Everyone will please not panic!

619
01:06:07,080 --> 01:06:08,593
Now...

620
01:06:08,799 --> 01:06:13,156
...prefects will lead their house
back to the dormitories.

621
01:06:13,839 --> 01:06:18,435
Teachers will follow me
to the dungeons.

622
01:06:29,040 --> 01:06:32,077
Gryffindors. keep up. please.
and stay alert.

623
01:06:32,279 --> 01:06:33,951
How could a troll get in?

624
01:06:34,160 --> 01:06:39,109
Not on its own. Trolls are really stupid.
Probably people playing jokes.

625
01:06:39,319 --> 01:06:43,153
-What?
-Hermione! She doesn't know.

626
01:06:54,760 --> 01:06:57,877
I think the troll's left the dungeon.

627
01:07:01,599 --> 01:07:03,669
It's going into the girls' bathroom.

628
01:07:33,440 --> 01:07:35,715
Hermione. move!

629
01:07:38,959 --> 01:07:42,918
Help! Help!

630
01:07:44,839 --> 01:07:46,830
Hey. pea brain!

631
01:07:58,759 --> 01:08:00,556
Help!

632
01:08:20,839 --> 01:08:23,114
Do something!

633
01:08:24,479 --> 01:08:28,267
-What?
-Anything!

634
01:08:28,880 --> 01:08:31,189
-Hurry up!
-Swish and flick.

635
01:08:31,400 --> 01:08:33,630
Wingardium L e viosa .

636
01:08:44,120 --> 01:08:46,031
Cool.

637
01:09:09,440 --> 01:09:12,159
Is it dead?

638
01:09:12,359 --> 01:09:16,113
I don't think so. Just knocked out.

639
01:09:22,119 --> 01:09:24,349
Troll boogers.

640
01:09:26,759 --> 01:09:30,149
Oh. my goodness!
Explain yourselves. both of you!

641
01:09:30,359 --> 01:09:34,796
-Well. what it is--
-|t's my fault. Professor McGonagall.

642
01:09:36,880 --> 01:09:38,029
Miss Granger?

643
01:09:38,879 --> 01:09:43,748
I went looking for the troll.
I thought I could handle it.

644
01:09:43,960 --> 01:09:45,757
But I was wrong.

645
01:09:45,959 --> 01:09:50,794
lf Harry and Ron hadn't come
and found me. I'd probably be dead.

646
01:09:51,760 --> 01:09:55,992
Be that as it may. it was
an extremely foolish thing to do.

647
01:09:56,199 --> 01:10:01,637
I expected more rational behavior
and am very disappointed in you.

648
01:10:01,839 --> 01:10:04,717
Five points will be taken
from Gryffindor...

649
01:10:04,919 --> 01:10:08,355
...for your serious lack of judgment.

650
01:10:08,800 --> 01:10:10,711
As for you two gentlemen...

651
01:10:10,919 --> 01:10:14,195
...| just hope you realize
how fortunate you are.

652
01:10:14,399 --> 01:10:17,675
Not many first-year students
could take on a troll...

653
01:10:17,879 --> 01:10:20,393
...and live to tell the tale.

654
01:10:20,640 --> 01:10:22,949
Five points...

655
01:10:24,279 --> 01:10:27,271
...will be awarded to each of you...

656
01:10:28,800 --> 01:10:31,758
...for sheer dumb luck.

657
01:10:37,120 --> 01:10:40,715
Perhaps you ought to go.
It might wake up.

658
01:10:48,199 --> 01:10:50,838
Take a bit of toast. mate. Go on.

659
01:10:51,039 --> 01:10:54,111
Ron's right.
You'll need your strength today.

660
01:10:54,319 --> 01:10:56,435
I'm not hungry.

661
01:10:56,999 --> 01:11:02,392
Good luck today. Potter.
You've proven yourself against a troll.

662
01:11:02,600 --> 01:11:05,637
A game of Ouidditch
should be easy work.

663
01:11:05,839 --> 01:11:08,831
Even if it is against Slytherin.

664
01:11:16,199 --> 01:11:19,475
-That explains the blood.
-B|ood?

665
01:11:19,879 --> 01:11:23,838
Last night. I'm guessing Snape let
the troll in as a diversion...

666
01:11:24,039 --> 01:11:26,599
...so he could get past that dog.

667
01:11:26,799 --> 01:11:29,438
But he got bit.
that's why he's limping.

668
01:11:29,680 --> 01:11:31,796
But why would anyone go near that dog?

669
01:11:32,440 --> 01:11:35,557
At Gringotts. Hagrid took
something out of the vault.

670
01:11:35,759 --> 01:11:38,876
Said it was Hogwarts business.
very secret.

671
01:11:39,079 --> 01:11:40,148
You're saying--

672
01:11:40,359 --> 01:11:44,671
That's what the dog's guarding.
That's what Snape wants.

673
01:11:57,279 --> 01:12:01,067
-Bit early for mail. isn't it?
-But I never get mail.

674
01:12:01,600 --> 01:12:03,079
Let's open it.

675
01:12:12,839 --> 01:12:14,033
It's a broomstick.

676
01:12:14,800 --> 01:12:18,759
That's not just a broomstick.
it's a Nimbus 2000!

677
01:12:20,160 --> 01:12:22,116
But who--?

678
01:12:42,880 --> 01:12:45,269
-Scared. Harry?
-A little.

679
01:12:45,480 --> 01:12:48,995
It's all right. I felt the same way
before my first game.

680
01:12:49,199 --> 01:12:52,555
-What happened?
-I don't really remember.

681
01:12:52,840 --> 01:12:55,400
I took a Bludger to the head
two minutes in.

682
01:12:55,600 --> 01:12:58,319
Woke up in hospital a week later.

683
01:13:19,600 --> 01:13:22,831
Welcome to Hogwarts' first
Ouidditch game of the season.

684
01:13:23,040 --> 01:13:27,556
Today's game.
Slytherin versus Gryffindor!

685
01:13:56,600 --> 01:13:58,955
The players take their positions...

686
01:13:59,160 --> 01:14:02,789
...as Madam Hooch steps onto
the field to begin the game!

687
01:14:02,999 --> 01:14:06,196
Now. I want a nice. clean game...

688
01:14:06,799 --> 01:14:09,108
...from all of you!

689
01:14:14,039 --> 01:14:16,837
The Bludgers are up.
followed by the Golden Snitch.

690
01:14:17,039 --> 01:14:19,633
Remember. the Snitch
is worth 150 points.

691
01:14:19,840 --> 01:14:23,469
The Seeker who catches the Snitch
ends the game.

692
01:14:29,359 --> 01:14:33,318
The Ouaffle is released
and the game begins!

693
01:14:51,239 --> 01:14:55,835
Angelina Johnson scores!
Ten points for Gryffindor!

694
01:15:00,799 --> 01:15:02,027
Well done!

695
01:15:06,239 --> 01:15:11,711
Slytherin takes the Ouaffle.
Bletchley passes to Captain Marcus Flint.

696
01:15:42,440 --> 01:15:45,113
Another 10 points to Gryffindor!

697
01:15:58,359 --> 01:16:00,156
Give me that!

698
01:16:30,319 --> 01:16:32,833
Take that side!

699
01:17:20,280 --> 01:17:23,397
What's going on
with Harry's broomstick?

700
01:17:31,959 --> 01:17:34,075
lt's Snape.
He's jinxing the broom!

701
01:17:34,279 --> 01:17:38,477
-Jinxing the broom? What do we do?
-Leave it to me.

702
01:17:59,360 --> 01:18:00,839
Come on. Hermione!

703
01:18:14,360 --> 01:18:17,955
Lacarnum Inflamarae.

704
01:18:24,759 --> 01:18:27,671
Fire! You're on fire!

705
01:18:44,800 --> 01:18:46,870
Go. go. go. go!

706
01:19:36,760 --> 01:19:38,990
Looks like he's gonna be sick.

707
01:19:40,039 --> 01:19:41,438
He's got the Snitch!

708
01:19:41,640 --> 01:19:45,553
Harry Potter receives 150 points
for catching the Snitch!

709
01:19:45,760 --> 01:19:47,352
Gryffindor wins!

710
01:20:29,159 --> 01:20:33,232
Nonsense! Why would Snape
put a curse on Harry's broom?

711
01:20:33,440 --> 01:20:37,194
Who knows? Why was he trying
to get past that three-headed dog?

712
01:20:37,399 --> 01:20:39,708
-Who told you about Fluffy?
-F|uffy?

713
01:20:39,920 --> 01:20:43,435
-That thing has a name?
-Of course he has a name. He's mine.

714
01:20:43,640 --> 01:20:48,714
I bought him off an Irishman.
l lent him to Dumbledore to guard--

715
01:20:48,920 --> 01:20:53,311
Shouldn't have said that.
No more questions! That's top-secret.

716
01:20:53,880 --> 01:20:57,714
But whatever Fluffy's guarding.
Snape's trying to steal it.

717
01:20:57,920 --> 01:21:01,230
Codswallop. Professor Snape
is a Hogwarts teacher.

718
01:21:01,719 --> 01:21:06,588
Teacher or not. I know a spell when
| see one. I've read all about them.

719
01:21:06,800 --> 01:21:10,236
You've got to keep eye contact.
and Snape wasn't blinking.

720
01:21:10,439 --> 01:21:12,589
Exactly.

721
01:21:13,239 --> 01:21:15,878
Now. you listen to me.
all three of you.

722
01:21:16,080 --> 01:21:20,551
You're meddling in things that ought
not to be meddled in. It's dangerous.

723
01:21:20,760 --> 01:21:25,629
What that dog is guarding is
between Dumbledore and Nicholas Flamel.

724
01:21:25,839 --> 01:21:27,192
Nicholas Flamel?

725
01:21:28,159 --> 01:21:32,675
I shouldn't have said that.
I should not have said that.

726
01:21:32,880 --> 01:21:36,793
Nicholas Flamel.
Who's Nicholas Flamel?

727
01:21:37,000 --> 01:21:38,911
I don't know.

728
01:21:57,000 --> 01:21:59,719
Merry Christmas
Merry Christmas

729
01:21:59,959 --> 01:22:02,632
