I don't know how you know.
but I assure you it is well protected.

966
01:47:39,200 --> 01:47:43,318
Now would you go back
to your dormitories? Ouietly.

967
01:47:51,279 --> 01:47:53,952
That was no stranger Hagrid met.
It was Snape.

968
01:47:54,159 --> 01:47:56,719
Which means he knows
how to get past Fluffy.

969
01:47:56,920 --> 01:48:00,629
-And with Dumbledore gone--
-Good afternoon.

970
01:48:02,600 --> 01:48:05,558
What would three young Gryffindors...

971
01:48:05,799 --> 01:48:09,917
...be doing inside on a day like this?

972
01:48:14,480 --> 01:48:17,870
-We were just--
-You ought to be careful.

973
01:48:18,399 --> 01:48:20,276
People will think you're...

974
01:48:24,399 --> 01:48:26,993
...up to something.

975
01:48:36,880 --> 01:48:38,791
Now what do we do?

976
01:48:38,999 --> 01:48:42,594
We go down the trap door. Tonight.

977
01:48:55,799 --> 01:48:57,198
Trevor.

978
01:48:57,519 --> 01:49:00,795
Trevor. go! You shouldn't be here!

979
01:49:01,039 --> 01:49:06,238
Neither should you.
You're sneaking out again. aren't you?

980
01:49:06,439 --> 01:49:10,227
-Nevi|le. listen. We were--
-No. I won't let you!

981
01:49:10,480 --> 01:49:14,871
You'll get Gryffindor into trouble again.
I'll fight you.

982
01:49:15,079 --> 01:49:19,197
Neville. I'm really sorry about this.
Petrificus Totalus.

983
01:49:26,839 --> 01:49:30,468
You're a little scary sometimes.
you know that?

984
01:49:30,720 --> 01:49:34,190
Brilliant. but scary.

985
01:49:34,839 --> 01:49:36,795
Let's go.

986
01:49:36,999 --> 01:49:41,072
-Sorry.
-|t's for your own good. you know.

987
01:49:46,279 --> 01:49:50,067
-You stood on my foot!
-Sorry.

988
01:49:53,799 --> 01:49:55,755
Alohomora.

989
01:50:07,279 --> 01:50:09,747
Wait a minute. He's...

990
01:50:10,920 --> 01:50:12,990
...snoring.

991
01:50:15,399 --> 01:50:20,712
Snape's already been here.
He's put a spell on the harp.

992
01:50:22,240 --> 01:50:25,118
It's got horrible breath.

993
01:50:27,599 --> 01:50:29,590
-We have to move its paw.
-What?

994
01:50:29,799 --> 01:50:31,152
Come on!

995
01:50:35,040 --> 01:50:37,031
Okay. Push.

996
01:50:59,240 --> 01:51:02,710
I'll go first. Don't follow
until I give you a sign.

997
01:51:02,920 --> 01:51:07,710
If something bad happens.
get yourselves out.

998
01:51:08,480 --> 01:51:11,790
Does it seem a bit quiet to you?

999
01:51:12,480 --> 01:51:14,232
The harp.

1000
01:51:14,880 --> 01:51:17,474
lt's stopped playing.

1001
01:51:27,120 --> 01:51:28,189
Jump!

1002
01:51:41,799 --> 01:51:45,269
Lucky this plant thing's here. really.

1003
01:51:59,120 --> 01:52:02,078
Stop moving. both of you.
This is Devil's Snare.

1004
01:52:02,280 --> 01:52:05,829
You have to relax. If you don't.
it will only kill you faster.

1005
01:52:06,039 --> 01:52:10,829
Kill us faster?
Oh. now I can relax!

1006
01:52:12,999 --> 01:52:14,273
Hermione!

1007
01:52:14,839 --> 01:52:18,468
-Now what are we gonna do?
-Just relax!

1008
01:52:18,679 --> 01:52:22,991
-Hermione. where are you?
-Do what I say! Trust me.

1009
01:52:29,799 --> 01:52:32,996
-Are you okay?
-Yeah. I'm fine.

1010
01:52:33,200 --> 01:52:36,112
-He's not relaxing. is he?
-Apparently not.

1011
01:52:36,319 --> 01:52:38,753
-We've gotta do something.
-What?

1012
01:52:38,960 --> 01:52:41,758
I remember reading something
in Herbology.

1013
01:52:42,599 --> 01:52:46,274
Devil's Snare. Devil's Snare.
lt's deadly fun...

1014
01:52:46,480 --> 01:52:50,678
...but will sulk in the sun!
That's it! It hates sunlight.

1015
01:52:50,920 --> 01:52:52,876
Lumus Solem.

1016
01:53:00,639 --> 01:53:03,107
-Ron. you okay?
-Yeah.

1017
01:53:05,720 --> 01:53:08,075
Lucky we didn't panic.

1018
01:53:08,799 --> 01:53:12,155
Lucky Hermione pays attention
in Herbology.

1019
01:53:13,720 --> 01:53:15,153
What is that?

1020
01:53:15,359 --> 01:53:18,908
I don't know. Sounds like wings.

1021
01:53:31,519 --> 01:53:34,829
Curious. I've never seen
birds like these.

1022
01:53:35,040 --> 01:53:38,510
They're not birds.
They're keys.

1023
01:53:38,720 --> 01:53:42,030
And I'll bet one of them
fits that door.

1024
01:53:45,359 --> 01:53:49,796
-What's this all about?
-I don't know.

1025
01:53:55,440 --> 01:53:57,396
Strange.

1026
01:53:57,799 --> 01:53:59,994
Alohomora!

1027
01:54:02,839 --> 01:54:04,989
Well. it was worth a try.

1028
01:54:05,200 --> 01:54:08,317
What will we do?
There must be a thousand keys.

1029
01:54:08,519 --> 01:54:12,273
We want a big. old-fashioned one.
Probably rusty.

1030
01:54:12,480 --> 01:54:15,756
| see it!
The one with the broken wing.

1031
01:54:19,200 --> 01:54:21,430
What's wrong?

1032
01:54:22,279 --> 01:54:23,712
It's too simple.

1033
01:54:23,920 --> 01:54:28,471
Go on! If Snape could catch it
on that old broomstick. you can.

1034
01:54:28,680 --> 01:54:32,070
You're the youngest Seeker
in a century.

1035
01:54:48,240 --> 01:54:51,118
This complicates things a bit.

1036
01:55:11,519 --> 01:55:13,350
Catch the key!

1037
01:55:17,600 --> 01:55:19,431
Hurry up!

1038
01:55:50,599 --> 01:55:55,070
I don't like this.
I don't like this at all.

1039
01:55:55,279 --> 01:55:58,316
Where are we? A graveyard.

1040
01:55:58,679 --> 01:56:01,193
This is no graveyard.

1041
01:56:08,400 --> 01:56:11,198
It's a chessboard.

1042
01:56:22,679 --> 01:56:24,510
There's the door.

1043
01:56:36,080 --> 01:56:37,513
Now what do we do?

1044
01:56:37,880 --> 01:56:41,839
It's obvious. isn't it? We've got
to play our way across the room.

1045
01:56:42,400 --> 01:56:45,995
Harry. you take
the empty bishop's square.

1046
01:56:46,319 --> 01:56:50,358
Hermione. you'll be
the queen-side castle.

1047
01:56:50,599 --> 01:56:54,478
As for me. I'll be a knight.

1048
01:57:01,359 --> 01:57:02,997
What happens now?

1049
01:57:03,759 --> 01:57:06,637
Well. white moves first.

1050
01:57:06,839 --> 01:57:08,636
And then...

1051
01:57:10,319 --> 01:57:11,513
...we play.

1052
01:57:21,680 --> 01:57:26,515
Ron. you don't suppose
this is going to be like...

1053
01:57:26,759 --> 01:57:30,149
...real wizard's chess. do you?

1054
01:57:30,519 --> 01:57:33,352
You there. d5.

1055
01:57:47,360 --> 01:57:48,873
Yes. Hermione.

1056
01:57:49,080 --> 01:57:53,949
I think this is gonna be
exactly like wizard's chess.

1057
01:57:59,640 --> 01:58:02,029
Castle to e4!

1058
01:58:05,519 --> 01:58:07,714
Pawn to c3!

1059
01:58:50,519 --> 01:58:54,353
-Wait a minute.
-You understand right. Harry.

1060
01:58:54,600 --> 01:58:59,116
Once I make my move.
the queen will take me.

1061
01:58:59,720 --> 01:59:01,950
Then you're free to check the king.

1062
01:59:02,160 --> 01:59:04,754
-No. Ron. no!
-What is it?

1063
01:59:05,359 --> 01:59:09,830
-He's going to sacrifice himself.
-No. there must be another way!

1064
01:59:10,039 --> 01:59:13,634
Do you wanna stop Snape
from getting that Stone or not?

1065
01:59:13,840 --> 01:59:17,276
Harry. it's you that has to go on.
I know it.

1066
01:59:17,759 --> 01:59:20,398
Not me. Not Hermione. You.

1067
01:59:30,240 --> 01:59:33,038
Knight to h3.

1068
01:59:53,120 --> 01:59:55,031
Check.

1069
02:00:22,999 --> 02:00:24,717
Ron!

1070
02:00:24,920 --> 02:00:30,472
No. don't move!
Don't forget. we're still playing.

1071
02:00:44,920 --> 02:00:46,148
Checkmate.

1072
02:01:05,279 --> 02:01:07,668
Take care of Ron.
Then go to the owlery.

1073
02:01:07,880 --> 02:01:11,589
Send a message to Dumbledore.
Ron's right.

1074
02:01:11,800 --> 02:01:13,597
l have to go on.

1075
02:01:14,080 --> 02:01:19,757
You'll be okay. Harry.
You're a great wizard. You really are.

1076
02:01:19,960 --> 02:01:22,349
Not as good as you.

1077
02:01:23,160 --> 02:01:27,790
Me? Books and cleverness.
There are more important things.

1078
02:01:28,959 --> 02:01:34,352
Friendship and bravery.
And. Harry. just be careful.

1079
02:02:10,879 --> 02:02:12,471
You?

1080
02:02:13,240 --> 02:02:16,915
No. it can't be.
Snape. he was the--

1081
02:02:17,119 --> 02:02:20,031
Yes. he does seem the type.
doesn't he?

1082
02:02:20,240 --> 02:02:23,232
Next to him. who would suspect...

1083
02:02:23,439 --> 02:02:27,193
...poor. stuttering
Professor Ouirrell?

1084
02:02:27,400 --> 02:02:32,554
But that day. during the Ouidditch match.
Snape tried to kill me.

1085
02:02:32,759 --> 02:02:35,432
No. dear boy. I tried to kill you!

1086
02:02:35,920 --> 02:02:39,913
lf Snape's cloak hadn't caught
fire and broken my eye contact...

1087
02:02:40,120 --> 02:02:42,236
...I would have succeeded.

1088
02:02:42,439 --> 02:02:45,317
Even with Snape muttering
his countercurse.

1089
02:02:45,519 --> 02:02:47,635
Snape was trying to save me?

1090
02:02:47,839 --> 02:02:52,959
I knew you were a danger to me.
especially after Halloween.

1091
02:02:53,160 --> 02:02:57,233
-Then you let the troll in!
-Very good. Potter. yes.

1092
02:02:57,439 --> 02:03:00,317
Snape. unfortunately. wasn't fooled.

1093
02:03:00,880 --> 02:03:05,635
While everyone ran about.
he went to the third floor to head me off.

1094
02:03:06,520 --> 02:03:09,876
He. of course. never trusted me again.

1095
02:03:10,840 --> 02:03:15,868
He rarely left me alone.
But he doesn't understand.

1096
02:03:16,079 --> 02:03:19,958
I'm never alone. Never.

1097
02:03:20,160 --> 02:03:24,073
Now. what does this mirror do?

1098
02:03:25,599 --> 02:03:27,635
| see what I desire.

1099
02:03:28,159 --> 02:03:32,391
| see myself holding the Stone.
But how do | get it?

1100
02:03:32,600 --> 02:03:34,670
Use the boy.

1101
02:03:35,439 --> 02:03:39,193
Come here. Potter! Now!

1102
02:03:50,799 --> 02:03:54,633
Tell me. what do you see?

1103
02:04:18,760 --> 02:04:21,069
What is it? What do you see?

1104
02:04:21,279 --> 02:04:26,228
l'm shaking hands with Dumbledore.
I've won the house cup.

1105
02:04:26,440 --> 02:04:27,919
He lies.

1106
02:04:28,400 --> 02:04:31,949
Tell the truth! What do you see?

1107
02:04:32,160 --> 02:04:36,358
-Let me speak to him.
-Master. you are not strong enough.

1108
02:04:36,600 --> 02:04:40,434
l have strength enough for this.

1109
02:04:57,880 --> 02:05:00,633
Harry Potter...

1110
02:05:00,840 --> 02:05:03,070
...we meet again.

1111
02:05:03,279 --> 02:05:04,632
Voldemort.

1112
02:05:04,840 --> 02:05:08,628
Yes. You see what I've become?

1113
02:05:08,879 --> 02:05:12,315
See what I must do to survive?

1114
02:05:12,520 --> 02:05:16,479
Live off another. A mere parasite.

1115
02:05:17,119 --> 02:05:20,316
Unicorn blood can sustain me...

1116
02:05:20,520 --> 02:05:24,035
...but it cannot give me
a body of my own.

1117
02:05:24,240 --> 02:05:27,630
But there is something that can.

1118
02:05:27,839 --> 02:05:33,277
Something that. conveniently enough.
lies in your pocket.

1119
02:05:33,640 --> 02:05:35,119
Stop him!

1120
02:05:39,960 --> 02:05:42,599
Don't be a fool.

1121
02:05:43,080 --> 02:05:46,072
Why suffer an horrific death...

1122
02:05:46,279 --> 02:05:49,749
...when you can join me and live?

1123
02:05:49,959 --> 02:05:50,994
Never!

1124
02:05:52,920 --> 02:05:57,516
Bravery. Your parents had it too.

1125
02:05:58,239 --> 02:06:01,390
Tell me. Harry...

1126
02:06:01,639 --> 02:06:05,348
...would you like to see
your mother and father again?

1127
02:06:05,599 --> 02:06:07,590
Together...

1128
02:06:07,799 --> 02:06:10,233
...we can bring them back.

1129
02:06:10,640 --> 02:06:15,156
All | ask is for something in return.

1130
02:06:21,599 --> 02:06:24,591
That's it. Harry.

1131
02:06:25,440 --> 02:06:29,149
There is no good and evil.

1132
02:06:29,359 --> 02:06:32,237
There is only power...

1133
02:06:32,439 --> 02:06:36,398
...and those too weak to seek it.

1134
02:06:37,040 --> 02:06:41,875
Together. we'll do
extraordinary things.

1135
02:06:42,280 --> 02:06:44,430
Just give me the Stone!

1136
02:06:46,960 --> 02:06:48,075
You liar!

1137
02:06:48,280 --> 02:06:50,316
Kill him!

1138
02:07:12,879 --> 02:07:17,999
-What is this magic?
-Fool. get the Stone!

1139
02:08:58,959 --> 02:09:01,348
Good afternoon. Harry.

1140
02:09:03,400 --> 02:09:07,712
-Tokens from your admirers?
-Admirers?

1141
02:09:07,920 --> 02:09:13,677
What happened in the dungeons between
you and Professor Ouirrell is a secret.

1142
02:09:13,880 --> 02:09:18,476
So. naturally. the whole school knows.

1143
02:09:20,719 --> 02:09:24,189
| see that your friend Ronald
has saved you the trouble...

1144
02:09:24,399 --> 02:09:27,118
...of opening your Chocolate Frogs.

1145
02:09:27,320 --> 02:09:30,198
Ron was here? Is he all right?
What about Hermione?

1146
02:09:30,399 --> 02:09:35,075
Fine. They're both just fine.

1147
02:09:35,640 --> 02:09:38,313
-What happened to the Stone?
-Re|ax. dear boy.

1148
02:09:38,639 --> 02:09:41,358
The Stone has been destroyed.

1149
02:09:41,599 --> 02:09:45,638
My friend Nicholas and l
have had a little chat...

1150
02:09:45,839 --> 02:09:49,627
...and agreed it was best all around.

1151
02:09:49,840 --> 02:09:53,515
But then. Flamel.
he'll die. won't he?

1152
02:09:55,479 --> 02:10:00,758
He has enough Elixir
to set his affairs in order.

1153
02:10:00,960 --> 02:10:04,032
But yes. he will die.

1154
02:10:04,240 --> 02:10:06,595
How is it I got the Stone. sir?

1155
02:10:06,799 --> 02:10:09,233
One minute I was staring
in the mirror and--

1156
02:10:09,439 --> 02:10:13,352
You see. only a person...

1157
02:10:13,639 --> 02:10:17,393
...who wanted to find the Stone.
find it...

1158
02:10:17,640 --> 02:10:21,997
...but not use it.
would be able to get it.

1159
02:10:22,920 --> 02:10:26,276
That is one of my more brilliant ideas.

1160
02:10:26,479 --> 02:10:31,314
And between you and me.
that is saying something.

1161
02:10:32,719 --> 02:10:37,713
Does that mean. with the Stone gone.
that Voldemort can never come back?

1162
02:10:37,920 --> 02:10:40,150
I'm afraid...

1163
02:10:41,519 --> 02:10:45,398
...there are ways
in which he can return.

1164
02:10:46,079 --> 02:10:48,547
Harry. do you know why...

1165
02:10:48,760 --> 02:10:52,594
...Professor Ouirrell couldn't bear
to have you touch him?

1166
02:10:52,799 --> 02:10:57,236
It was because of your mother.
She sacrificed herself for you.

1167
02:10:57,759 --> 02:11:00,831
And that kind of act leaves a mark.

1168
02:11:01,039 --> 02:11:04,668
No. this kind of mark cannot be seen.

1169
02:11:04,879 --> 02:11:09,589
-|t lives in your very skin.
-What is it?

1170
02:11:10,399 --> 02:11:13,994
Love. Harry. Love.

1171
02:11:21,719 --> 02:11:25,678
Bertie Bott's Every Flavor Beans.

1172
02:11:25,880 --> 02:11:30,351
l was most unfortunate in my youth
to come across a vomit-flavored one.

1173
02:11:30,600 --> 02:11:33,751
And since then.
I've lost my liking for them.

1174
02:11:33,959 --> 02:11:37,190
But I think I could be safe...

1175
02:11:37,399 --> 02:11:39,674
...with a nice toffee.

1176
02:11:43,599 --> 02:11:45,078
Alas!

1177
02:11:45,759 --> 02:11:47,795
Earwax.

1178
02:12:02,400 --> 02:12:05,437
-All right there. Ron?
-All right. You?

1179
02:12:06,520 --> 02:12:09,114
All right. Hermione?

1180
02:12:09,759 --> 02:12:11,511
Never better.

1181
02:12:26,680 --> 02:12:29,035
Another year gone.

1182
02:12:29,759 --> 02:12:34,116
And now. as I understand it.
the house cup needs awarding.

1183
02:12:34,319 --> 02:12:36,833
And the points stand thus:

1184
02:12:37,039 --> 02:12:42,591
ln fourth place.
Gryffindor with 312 points.

1185
02:12:44,480 --> 02:12:49,918
Third place.
Hufflepuff with 352 points.

1186
02:12:54,999 --> 02:12:56,717
ln second place...

1187
02:12:56,920 --> 02:13:01,516
...Ravenclaw with 426 points.

1188
02:13:06,959 --> 02:13:08,597
And in first place...

1189
02:13:08,920 --> 02:13:14,119
...with 472 points. Slytherin house.

1190
02:13:19,480 --> 02:13:21,596
Nice one. mate.

1191
02:13:25,279 --> 02:13:29,192
Yes. well done. Slytherin.
Well done.

1192
02:13:29,439 --> 02:13:33,557
However. recent events must
be taken into account.

1193
02:13:33,759 --> 02:13:38,514
And l have a few last-minute points
to award.

1194
02:13:39,119 --> 02:13:44,398
To Miss Hermione Granger.
for the cool use of intellect...

1195
02:13:44,600 --> 02:13:47,273
...while others were in grave peril...

1196
02:13:47,960 --> 02:13:50,110
...50 points.

1197
02:13:50,999 --> 02:13:52,227
Good job.

1198
02:13:59,640 --> 02:14:05,431
Second. to Mr. Ronald Weasley.
for the best-played game of chess...

1199
02:14:05,920 --> 02:14:10,948
...that Hogwarts has seen
these many years. 50 points.

1200
02:14:15,399 --> 02:14:17,355
And third...

1201
02:14:17,880 --> 02:14:20,633
...to Mr. Harry Potter...

1202
02:14:20,840 --> 02:14:24,958
...for pure nerve
and outstanding courage...

1203
02:14:25,519 --> 02:14:30,195
...l award Gryffindor house 60 points.

1204
02:14:38,159 --> 02:14:39,990
We're tied with Slytherin!

1205
02:14:40,199 --> 02:14:45,956
Finally. it takes a great deal of bravery
to stand up to your enemies...

1206
02:14:46,159 --> 02:14:49,868
...but a great deal more
to stand up to your friends.

1207
02:14:50,079 --> 02:14:52,912
l award 10 points...

1208
02:14:53,119 --> 02:14:56,191
...to Neville Longbottom.

1209
02:15:08,999 --> 02:15:12,275
Assuming that my calculations
are correct...

1210
02:15:12,480 --> 02:15:16,837
...I believe that a change
of decoration is in order.

1211
02:15:21,680 --> 02:15:24,911
Gryffindor wins the house cup.

1212
02:16:01,400 --> 02:16:04,597
Come on. now.
Hurry up. you'll be late.

1213
02:16:04,799 --> 02:16:08,917
Train's leaving. Go on.
Come on. hurry up.

1214
02:16:14,120 --> 02:16:17,271
-Come on. Harry.
-One minute.

1215
02:16:23,279 --> 02:16:26,874
Thought you were leaving
without saying goodbye. did you?

1216
02:16:29,960 --> 02:16:31,712
This is for you.

1217
02:16:47,800 --> 02:16:49,836
Thanks. Hagrid.

1218
02:16:55,439 --> 02:16:59,671
Go on. On with you. On with you now.
Oh. listen. Harry.

1219
02:17:00,080 --> 02:17:04,358
If that dolt of a cousin of yours.
Dudley. gives you any grief...

1220
02:17:04,600 --> 02:17:07,160
...you could always threaten him...

1221
02:17:07,359 --> 02:17:10,112
...with a nice pair of ears
to go with his tail.

1222
02:17:10,319 --> 02:17:15,188
But we're not allowed to do magic
away from Hogwarts. You know that.

1223
02:17:15,640 --> 02:17:19,792
I do. But your cousin don't. do he?

1224
02:17:25,080 --> 02:17:28,072
Feels strange to be going home.
doesn't it?

1225
02:17:28,280 --> 02:17:30,271
I'm not going home.

